<item>
            <title>[JDK-8297632] InputStream.transferTo() method should specify what the return value should be when the number of bytes transfered is larger than Long.MAX_VALUE</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8297632</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>The javadoc of InputStream.transferTo only briefly states the expectations of the return value:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; @return the number of bytes transferred&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
It&amp;#39;s possible that the inpustream instance could transfer more data than what can be returned as a long value. &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
It would help to have the API specify what the expectations are in such cases.</description>
