                            <comment id="14541062" author="roboduke" created="Mon, 28 Nov 2022 17:05:52 -0800"  >A pull request was submitted for review.&lt;br/&gt;
URL: &lt;a href=&quot;https://git.openjdk.org/jdk/pull/11403&quot;&gt;https://git.openjdk.org/jdk/pull/11403&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Date: 2022-11-29 00:56:58 +0000</comment>
                            <comment id="14540730" author="bpb" created="Mon, 28 Nov 2022 13:03:35 -0800"  >While it looks as if the implementation of InputStream::transferTo can handle transferring more than Long.MAX_VALUE bytes, in that case it appears that the variable holding the number of bytes transferred will overflow a long once more than Long.MAX_VALUE bytes have been transferred, hence the value returned will be erroneous.</comment>
                            <comment id="14540332" author="jpai" created="Fri, 25 Nov 2022 03:41:15 -0800"  >Alan noted that the getXXXSpace methods in java.nio.file.FileStore is one example where we have a similar case of returning long values and those methods currently state:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; If the total number of&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;     * bytes in the file store is greater than {@link Long#MAX_VALUE}, then&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;     * {@code Long.MAX_VALUE} will be returned.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
A similar approach could perhaps be taken here.&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
